Package: tukeyAdEnet
Type: Package
Title: Robust Adaptive Elastic Net Regression via Tukey's Biweight Loss
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Ramakrushna", "Mishra",
           email = "rkmishra.stat@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
           comment = "Indian Institute of Management Lucknow"))
Description: Fits sparse linear regression models that are robust to outliers
    in the response and in the design matrix. The estimator minimises a
    redescending Tukey's biweight loss subject to an adaptive elastic net
    penalty, combining the exact-zero downweighting of gross outliers with
    the oracle variable-selection properties of adaptively weighted L1/L2
    penalties. Models are fitted with a coordinate-wise proximal AdaGrad
    algorithm and the regularisation parameters are selected automatically
    by minimising a robust Bayesian information criterion (RBIC) over a
    two-dimensional tuning grid, avoiding cross-validation under
    contamination. See Maronna, Martin, Yohai & Salibian-Barrera (2019,
    ISBN:978-1119214687) for background on redescending M-estimators and
    Zou & Zhang (2009) <doi:10.1214/09-AOS699> for adaptive elastic net
    penalisation.
